== Monuments on the parallel ==
[[File:Canada US border.JPG|thumb|right|The [[Peace Arch]] border]]
*In North America, the westernmost monument on the 49th parallel is the Point Roberts Boundary Monument near the corner of Marine Drive and Roosevelt Way in the [[Point Roberts, Washington|Point Roberts]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]] exclave south of [[Delta, British Columbia|Delta]], [[British Columbia]].
*The [[Peace Arch]] is a large monument between [[Surrey, British Columbia|Surrey]], British Columbia, and [[Blaine, Washington|Blaine]], Washington. It is the centerpiece of [[Peace Arch Park]].
*[[Waterton-Glacier International Peace Park]] in Alberta and Montana
*The [[International Peace Garden]] is located at the border between [[Manitoba]] and [[North Dakota]], about midway between the nearby communities of [[Boissevain, Manitoba]] and [[Dunseith, North Dakota]]. It has as its focal point the [[International Peace Garden|Peace Tower]] (actually four identical monuments 120 feet (36.6 m) tall set parallel only a few feet apart, two on each side of the border, giving the appearance of a double tower from most vantage points in the Garden).
*The Stadtgarten in [[Karlsruhe]], Germany, marks the 49th parallel with a stone and painted line.
