{{NASTRO comment}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Aichi}} [[Category:Background asteroids|005908]] [[Category:Discoveries by Toshimasa Furuta]] [[Category:Discoveries by Yoshikane Mizuno]] [[Category:Minor planets named for places]] [[Category:Named minor planets]] [[Category:Astronomical objects discovered in 1989|19891020]]

The '''Abas River''' ({{Lang-grc|{{polytonic|Ἄβας}}}}), was a river of [[Kingdom of Iberia|Iberia in Asia]], mentioned by [[Plutarch]] (Plut. ''Pomp.'' 35) and [[Dio Cassius]] (37.3) as crossed by [[Pompey]], on his expedition into the [[Caucasus|Caucasian regions]]. Its course was east of the [[Cambyses]] (likely the modern [[Iori (river)|Iori]]); and it seems to be the same as the "Alazonius" or "Alazon" of [[Strabo]] and [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]] which fell into the Cambyses just above its confluence with the [[Kura (Caspian Sea)|Cyrus]] (modern Kura). Thus, likely the modern [[Alazani]] River. The [[Battle of the Abas]] was fought on a plain adjacent to the river in 65 BCE.
==References== {{SmithDGRG|title=Abas}}
