The '''geology of [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]]''' is part of the overall Volcanic Caribbees grouping of the Lesser Antilles island arc. The oldest rocks are volcanic and sedimentary rocks form the [[Pliocene]] or [[Miocene]].<ref>{{cite book |author=Donovan, Steven K.; Jackson, Trevor A.|year=1994|title=Caribbean Geology: An Introduction|publisher=University of West Indies|p=171-173}}</ref>

