The '''University of Puerto Rico''' ('''UPR''') is the main [[public university]] system of [[Puerto Rico]] and a [[List of government-owned corporations of Puerto Rico|government-owned corporation of Puerto Rico]]. It consists of 11 campuses and has approximately 58,000 students and 5,300 faculty members.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hoy.upr.edu/ |title=La Universidad Hoy |publisher=Hoy.upr.edu |date= |accessdate=2010-07-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100127083517/http://hoy.upr.edu/ |archivedate=2010-01-27 |df= }}</ref> UPR has the largest and most diverse academic offerings in Puerto Rico and the [[Caribbean]], with 472 [[academic program]]s of which 32 lead to a [[doctorate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acweb.upr.edu/vpit/about_folder/biomedical.pdf/ |accessdate=October 25, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100610121152/http://acweb.upr.edu/vpit/about_folder/biomedical.pdf |archivedate=June 10, 2010 }}</ref>
