{{short description|river in People's Republic of China}} {{for|the river in Afghanistan|Khulm River}} {{Infobox river | name = Tashkurgan River | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = China Xinjiang | pushpin_map_caption= The Mouth of Tashkurgan River | pushpin_map_relief = no | source1 = [[Karakoram]] | source1_location = | source1_elevation = | source1_coordinates= {{coord|37.316613|N|75.412488|E}} | mouth = [[Yarkand River]] | mouth_coordinates = {{coord|37.8108|N|76.2009|E|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:CN|display=it}} | mouth_elevation = | progression = {{RYarkand}} | tributaries_left = Kalaqi Ku'er River | tributaries_right = | waterbodies = | subdivision_type1 = Country | subdivision_name1 = [[China]] | subdivision_type2 = Province | subdivision_name2 = [[Xinjiang]] | length = 190 km | discharge1_avg = | basin_size = | basin_landmarks = [[Tashkurgan Town]] }} The '''Tashkurgan River''' ({{zh|c=塔什库尔干河}}; [[pinyin]] ''Tǎshíkù'ěrgàn hé'') is a [[river]] in the [[Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region]] of western [[People's Republic of China|China]]. The Tashkurgan River runs through [[Tashkurgan Tajik Autonomous County]] and is one of the [[tributaries]] of the [[Yarkand River]] in the [[Tarim Basin]].
The river is formed by the joining of several mountain streams originating in the [[Karakoram]] range and northern [[Hindu Kush]] mountains. It flows due north until the [[Tashkorgan Town]].<ref name="Gregory1977">{{citation |last=Gregory |first=Patrick T |title=Life-history Parameters of the Red-sided Garter Snake (Thamnophis Sirtalis Parietalis) in an Extreme Environment, the Interlake Region of Manitoba |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F3QfAQAAIAAJ |year=1977 |publisher=National Museums of Canada |isbn=978-0-662-00002-0}}</ref> Then it turns right flowing through the mountains and joins the [[Yarkand River]].
